In [[Kibology]], '''wackyparsing''' is the practice of misreading text to humorous effect (perhaps deliberately), especially in line with traditional [[absurdism|absurdist]] Kibological humor.  The term has its origins in the [[computer science]] term ''parsing''.  

Though wackyparsing as a concept probably originated on [[alt.religion.kibology]] at least as early as 1998[http://groups.google.com/groups?hl=en&q=wackyparsing&qt_s=Search], the term has come to have wider usage, particularly on [[USENET]].  The typical usage is found in the phrase ''I wackyparsed that as...''

